args: {player_name} and Luca are showing\nLaranoa around a human town.
Ordinarily, Rolf would have remained\nto watch over the village, but today\nhe was given special dispensation.
Man, human towns are LOADED\nwith cool stuff!
Ha ha, I'm glad you're enjoying yourselves.
Who knew fish tasted so good?!
And that flea market? WAAAY better\nthan what we have back home!
Yeah, this town is pretty great.
I really wanna know more about human\nculture now.
I was hoping you might tell me where—
Easy boy. Sorry, he didn't mean to\nstartle you.
You need to keep better control\nof your mutt!
Rolf's not one to bark for no reason.\nSomething must have set him off.
Do you maybe have something\ndangerous on you?
Oh, you dropped something.\n...Is that a knife?
The blade is covered in poison!
He's getting away! I bet he's an assassin\nafter {player_name}!
I doubt we'll catch him now...\nHe's in the thick of the crowd.
Don't worry, we'll handle this. Rolf!
*pant* *pant* Damn it! I would've\ngotten away with it if not for that\nmeddling dog!
Better lie low here for a while.\nI'll need to think up a new plan\nto get—
Dammit... Did you follow my scent?!
Nevermind! You've gotten in my\nway for the last time—DIE!
I've got it from here, Rolf! HAH!
Heh. Once you're in our sights,\nyou're done for.
Now let's turn this guy in and\nget back to {player_name}.
Thanks for saving me, you two.
I've asked Cleo to cook a thank-you\nmeal for you. She's making something\nspecial for you too, Rolf.
You two really get each other, don't you?
Yup! In my village, it's really common\nto take a dog with you when you go\nout hunting.
Being able to work in perfect sync is\ncrucial—and it helps a bunch when\nyou're best buds.
Me and Rolf have been through the\ngrinder together.
Yeah. See, all hunters end up with dogs\neventually, but it's different when you're\nchosen to be the next chief.
You're with the pup from the moment\nit's born, and you have to go through\ntraining together.
That's how me and Rolf's story starts.
We did it all; running gauntlets,\nfighting fiends—we even sat\nunder freezing waterfalls!
Wow... It's no wonder your bond is\nso strong.
It wasn't easy at first, though.
He was a really naughty puppy.\nHe never listened to me at all.
I never would have guessed, seeing him\nnow. What changed?
Well, we were hunting one night as\npart of our training. Rolf was NOT\nhappy to be there.
We were in pursuit, but I caught my\nfoot on a root and totally messed\nup my ankle.
Oh yeah, it was bad. I couldn't even\nmove—I honestly thought it was the end.
Nobody else was around.\nJust me, Rolf, and the night.
So, even though I knew he wouldn't listen,\nI asked him to go get help.
He sure did. For the first time ever,\nhe listened to me. Help was there\nin no time.

Then, once my ankle was healed,
we started absolutely NAILING
our training. Rolf never ignored
me again.
And now we're best buds! Ha ha!

I still don't know WHY that was the
moment everything changed, though.
Why'd he start listening then?
And why'd he keep listening after?
I was wondering the same thing.\nPersonalities don't usually change\nthat quickly.
Do you think it might be because\nthat was the first time you really\nrelied on him?
Think about it: nobody wants to be\nordered around, especially if they\ndon't feel valued.

But if you show someone your trust and
respect, and really depend on them,
then they WANT to help. I think
that's what happened to Rolf.
Now that you mention it, I was really\nhappy the first time everyone depended\non me when we were out hunting, too.
I'd been on the fence about agreeing to\nbe the next chief, but that feeling made\nme decide to accept.
I was so happy to be able to help\neveryone... And I wanted to keep\nfeeling that way, you know?

Thanks, {player_name}.
I'm really glad I remembered
what made me wanna lead
in the first place.
I might doubt myself sometimes,\nbut I just gotta push on!
It sounds like you're out from under\nthe clouds.
Dang right! And don't worry Rolf, I haven't\nforgotten about you. You're the reason I\ncan get back up whenever I fall.
Laranoa, Rolf; your dinner is ready.
